Iâ€™m half Scottish with Irish and then half Native American so in the warm months Iâ€™m very tan/ dark but once winter hits the Scottish / Irish in me comes out so since I donâ€™t see the sun much. So I tan in the winter to keep my skin the color Iâ€™m used to being .  I prefer self tanner because I donâ€™t want skin damage . I can walk to the mail box and come back with intense tan lines

For me, I notice that when I'm darker in the summer, "flaws" of the skin are less noticeable. Bruises, cellulite, etc...

Self tanning is great to me because it's like make up for the body. I'm super light complected but in the sun I can get pretty dark, and stretch marks and scars can annoyingly look more aggravted from sun exposure. With self tanner, even if I'm naturally tanned from the sun, it covers those issues like concealer or foundation, and it can be used to contour the body and give the illusion of being more slim. Even my fam and girlfriends blessed with way more melanin than me, use self tanner for those reasons (Jackie aina has a video about using it to even out her skin tone, etc...).

Melanin abundant skin is so beautiful and it should be embraced on the people born with it naturally not just the ones who completley alter their appearance and call it a look.
